The paper deals with the problem of linking and integrating large and complex data collections, which is a common issue in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a novel clustering technique that incorporates temporal constraints, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of similarity graphs and unsupervised techniques also suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of statistical learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with historical data sets, which may be of interest to researchers in the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
